article.description: Devonte Patterson had 25 points as Prairie View rolled past Alcorn State 86-66 in the Southwestern Athletic Conference Tourney quarterfinals on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Patterson leads Prairie View over Alcorn St. 86-66
article.linkText: Patterson leads Prairie View over Alcorn St. 86-66
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas -- Devonte Patterson had 25 points as Prairie View rolled past Alcorn State 86-66 in the Southwestern Athletic Conference Tourney quarterfinals on Tuesday night. Chance Ellis had 11 points for Prairie View (20-12). Dennis Jones added 11 points, seven assists and five steals. Taishaun Johnson had 11 points for the home team. Maurice Howard had 21 points for the Braves (10-21). Reginal Johnson added 13 points and seven rebounds. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
